</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="638" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[113,1090,395,1316]" pageId="11" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,365,1131,1155]" pageId="11" pageNumber="638">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kejval, 2011" authorityName="Kejval" authorityYear="2011" box="[372,537,1133,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Notoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[372,537,1133,1156]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="638">Notoxus hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[544,628,1132,1155]" pageId="11" pageNumber="638" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished from all members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krekich-Strassoldo" authorityYear="1914" box="[230,338,1165,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Notoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis box="[230,338,1165,1188]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="638">N. indicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by rather distinctive colouration of the elytra, shape and modified setation of the male protibiae and by morphology of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="638" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[113,1090,395,1316]" pageId="11" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,241,1228,1252]" pageId="11" pageNumber="638">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kejval" authorityYear="2011" box="[426,495,1229,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Notoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis box="[426,495,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="638">hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(merry, hilarious); named in reference to the conspicuous markings of the elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
